</emphasis>
Payson Canyon, Payson, 
<collectingRegion id="4991F8327B1AFF85FD19F9B3FD0BDE6D" box="[693,757,1635,1659]" country="United States of America" name="Utah" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Utah</collectingRegion>
County, 
<collectingRegion id="4991F8327B1AFF85FCCFF9B3FC58DE6D" box="[867,934,1635,1659]" country="United States of America" name="Utah" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Utah</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA36D07B1AFF85FF6CF953FEB6DECD" blockId="40.[192,1440,1635,1755]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B1AFF85FF6CF953FE66DE8D" bold="true" box="[192,408,1667,1691]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Type label data.</emphasis>
“ 
<typeStatus id="54EE88727B1AFF85FE0BF953FDEBDE8D" box="[423,533,1667,1691]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Holotype</typeStatus>
[male] 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D537B1AFF85FDC1F953FC41DE8D" authorityName="dos Passos and Grey" authorityYear="1945" box="[621,959,1667,1691]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="atlantis" subSpecies="wasatchia">Speyeria atlantis wasatchia</taxonomicName>
Cyril F. dos Passos and L. Paul Grey; 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D537B1AFF85FA29F953FE05DEAD" authority="Edw. Det. Gunder" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Argynnis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chitone">A. chitone Edw. Det. Gunder</taxonomicName>
; Payson Canyon, Payson, 
<collectingRegion id="4991F8327B1AFF85FC9FF973FC8CDEAD" box="[819,882,1699,1723]" country="United States of America" name="Utah" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Utah</collectingRegion>
VII.16.32; Col. Pfouts; J. D. Gunder Collection Ac. 34998”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA36D07B1AFF85FF6CF8D3FADADF6D" blockId="40.[192,1440,1795,1916]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B1AFF85FF6CF8D3FD1ADF0D" bold="true" box="[192,740,1795,1819]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Identification, taxonomy, and variation.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C554D537B1AFF85FD45F8D4FBC0DF0D" authorityName="dos Passos and Grey" authorityYear="1945" box="[745,1086,1795,1819]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="hesperis" subSpecies="wasatchia">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B1AFF85FD45F8D4FBC0DF0D" box="[745,1086,1795,1819]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Speyeria hesperis wasatchia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B1AFF85FB75F8D4FA92DF0D" box="[1241,1388,1795,1819]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">
S. h. 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D537B1AFF85FAB8F8D3FA92DF0D" box="[1300,1388,1795,1819]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Argynnis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chitone">chitone</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and was considered a synonym (as 
<taxonomicName id="4C554D537B1AFF85FD92F8F4FC8CDF2D" box="[574,882,1827,1851]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Speyeria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="atlantis" subSpecies="chitone">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B1AFF85FD92F8F4FC8CDF2D" box="[574,882,1827,1851]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">Speyeria atlantis chitone</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by Hammond (1991). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC44B217B1AFF85FB22F8F3FA97DF2D" author="Scott, J. A. &amp; N. G. Kondla &amp; S. M. Spomer" box="[1166,1385,1827,1851]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" pagination="1 - 31" refId="ref45136" refString="Scott, J. A., N. G. Kondla, and S. M. Spomer. 1998. Speyeria hesperis and Speyeria atlantis are distinct species. Papilio 8: 1 - 31." type="journal article" year="1998">Scott et al. (1998)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC44B217B1AFF85FF6CF893FE90DF4D" author="Pelham, J." box="[192,366,1859,1883]" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" refId="ref43702" refString="Pelham, J. 2008. Catalogue of the butterflies of the United States and Canada. Journal of Research on the Lepidoptera 40: xiv + 658 p." type="book" year="2008">Pelham (2008)</bibRefCitation>
list 
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B1AFF85FE32F894FDAADF4D" box="[414,596,1859,1883]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">S. h. wasatchia</emphasis>
as a synonym of 
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B1AFF85FCB6F894FC59DF4D" box="[794,935,1859,1883]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">S. h. tetonia</emphasis>
. Ventral hindwing spots of 
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B1AFF85FB47F894FA5EDF4D" box="[1259,1440,1859,1883]" italics="true" pageId="40" pageNumber="39">S. h. wasatchia</emphasis>
are typically unsilvered but there are silvered forms. Adult wingspan ranges from 
<quantity id="4CAD9B357B1AFF85FB0FF8B3FADEDF6D" box="[1187,1312,1891,1915]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="40" pageNumber="39" unit="mm" value="55.0" valueMax="60.0" valueMin="50.0">50-60 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA36D07B1BFF84FF6CFF13FD1ED8CD" blockId="41.[192,736,195,219]" box="[192,736,195,219]" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B1BFF84FF6CFF13FEDED8CD" bold="true" box="[192,288,195,219]" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Range.</emphasis>
Known from a few localities in 
<collectingRegion id="4991F8327B1BFF84FD35FF13FD22D8CD" box="[665,732,195,219]" country="United States of America" name="Utah" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Utah</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEA36D07B1BFF84FF6CFED3FAAAD90D" blockId="41.[192,1364,259,283]" box="[192,1364,259,283]" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="B921EAC27B1BFF84FF6CFED3FE96D90D" bold="true" box="[192,360,259,283]" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Life history.</emphasis>
This subspecies can be encountered at elevations above 
<quantity id="4CAD9B357B1BFF84FBBEFED3FB88D90D" box="[1042,1142,259,283]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.286" pageId="41" pageNumber="40" unit="ft" value="7.5">7,500 ft.</quantity>
in northern 
<collectingRegion id="4991F8327B1BFF84FAA1FED3FAAED90D" box="[1293,1360,259,283]" country="United States of America" name="Utah" pageId="41" pageNumber="40">Utah</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
